{
  "texts": [
    "SPICE 36 differs from BLEU by focusing on semantic accuracy in image caption generation rather than mere word or phrase matching, providing a comprehensive assessment of generated description quality.",
    "Score 37 utilizes the pre-trained BERT model to compute the semantic similarity between generated and reference text.",
    "It excels at assessing semantic match within the overall context, providing a nuanced and semantically oriented evaluation of model performance.",
    "The classification metrics were employed to supplement the languagebased metrics, providing a more comprehensive evaluation of the model's ability to accurately identify diseases.",
    "Initially, we manually constructed a keyword dictionary for ophthalmic conditions."
  ]
}